## BUG #6: PARTIAL RECORD ON DISK FULL

### The Issue

```go
func writeWALRecordDirect(w *bufio.Writer, msg *WALMessage) error {
    var hdr [8]byte
    binary.LittleEndian.PutUint32(hdr[0:4], walRecordMagic)
    binary.LittleEndian.PutUint32(hdr[4:8], uint32(payloadSize))
    if _, err := w.Write(hdr[:]); err != nil {
        return err  // <-- Partial data in buffer!
    }
    // ... more writes ...
}
```

If any write fails, previous writes sit in bufio.Writer. Next call appends, corrupting the file.

### Fix Strategy: Two-Phase Write

```go
func writeWALRecordDirect(w *bufio.Writer, msg *WALMessage) error {
    // Phase 1: Prepare all data in a buffer
    var buf bytes.Buffer

    // Write to temporary buffer
    payloadSize := 8 + 2 + len(msg.MetricName) + 1 + 4
    for _, s := range msg.Selector {
        payloadSize += 1 + len(s)
    }

    // Write magic + length
    var hdr [8]byte
    binary.LittleEndian.PutUint32(hdr[0:4], walRecordMagic)
    binary.LittleEndian.PutUint32(hdr[4:8], uint32(payloadSize))
    buf.Write(hdr[:])

    // ... prepare payload in buf ...

    // Phase 2: Compute CRC
    crc := crc32.NewIEEE()
    payload := buf.Bytes()[8:]  // Skip magic + length
    crc.Write(payload)

    // Phase 3: Atomic write (buffer is complete, write as one unit)
    if _, err := w.Write(buf.Bytes()); err != nil {
        return err
    }

    var crcBuf [4]byte
    binary.LittleEndian.PutUint32(crcBuf[:], crc.Sum32())
    if _, err := w.Write(crcBuf[:]); err != nil {
        return err
    }

    return nil
}
```

