## BUG #4: SILENT DATA LOSS ON BACKPRESSURE

### The Issue

```
Channel size = 65536 / walNumShards
With 4 workers: 65536 / 4 = 16384 per shard
At 100k msg/sec across 4 workers: 25k msg/sec per shard
Channel fills in: 16384 / 25000 = 0.65 seconds
```

Every drop violates the durability guarantee, but drops are only logged every 10k drops.

### Fix Strategy: Implement Real Backpressure

```go
// In lineprotocol.go DecodeLine:
if Keys.Checkpoints.FileFormat == "wal" {
    msg := &WALMessage{
        MetricName: string(st.metricBuf),
        Cluster:    cluster,
        Node:       host,
        Selector:   append([]string{}, st.selector...),
        Value:      metric.Value,
        Timestamp:  time.Unix(),
    }

    // Option 1: Block on full (applies backpressure)
    if !SendWALMessageBlocking(msg, 1*time.Second) {
        cclog.Errorf("[METRICSTORE]> WAL timeout for %s/%s metric %s, dropping",
            cluster, host, string(st.metricBuf))
        // Now we know it was dropped, and metrics show it
    }

    // Option 2: Increase channel size dynamically
    // or use unbounded queue
}

// In walCheckpoint.go:
func SendWALMessageBlocking(msg *WALMessage, timeout time.Duration) bool {
    if walShardChs == nil {
        return false
    }
    shard := walShardIndex(msg.Cluster, msg.Node)

    select {
    case walShardChs[shard] <- msg:
        return true
    case <-time.After(timeout):
        return false  // Timeout, metric dropped (with explicit error logged)
    }
}

// Or: Increase channel buffer significantly
const chBufSize = 1 << 20  // 1 million messages, ~100MB
```

